narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Knowledge of the diverse contours of second-century Christianity and the history of modern scholarship on it

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Was not as organized. Syllabus was "flexible" but notifications of submission details/deadlines/grading criteria/grades are absent.
The course was well organized and addressed many of the central and peripheral issues of modern scholarship on 2nd century Christianity.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: To a student with the requisite training and interests, yes.
